<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\re_scripted_interactions\re_si_stranded_ship_lagufaeth</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>34</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 0] whistles from high in the rigging and points frantically to port. "Look, captain! Look!"

Your crew gathers to peer into the distance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm going aboard."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Continue on our course."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 2] salutes. "Aye, captain. Probably for the best. No telling what's lying in wait out there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>The crew ready the skiff, and you oar your way across the ocean swells towards the listing junk.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fire the cannons. Scare those creatures away."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>The shot arcs over the junk's deck and whizzes past its hull, splashing into the water all around the wreck.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Ship] shudders as the cannons fire. 

Unfortunately, a few shots crash through the hull, just beneath the waterline. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>You reach the ship safely and scale the side of the ship...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>The crew ready the skiff, and you oar your way across the ocean swells towards the listing junk.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you approach, the lagufaeth hiss and gurgle at you from the deck. A few produce blowguns and quickly fill the air with a rain of brightly-feathered darts.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>From behind you, [SkillCheck 0] cries out. You look back to see your companion pull a feathered needle the length of a dagger from between the ribs. You take the dart and throw it into the water as [SkillCheck 0] attends to the bleeding.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>One of the darts strikes you, punching through gear and skin alike. You tear it from your flesh and throw the dagger-length projectile overboard. You clasp a hand over the wound, and blood seeps from between your fingers.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>The darts pelt the skiff, but none of them strike you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Use spyglass.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Bring us closer. I want a better look."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>You look out upon the ship, a ruined junk sporting faded Deadfire Company colors. The sails hang limp and shredded, and cracks mar the barnacle-spotted planks.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 1] salutes. "Aye, captain."

Rigging tightens and sails creek as [Player Ship] approaches the unknown vessel.

The ship slowly looms closer, a ruined junk sporting faded Deadfire Company colors. The sails hang limp and shredded, and cracks mar the barnacle-spotted planks.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>A lanky, agile creature scales the side of the ship, its four arms hauling it over the railing and onto the deck. The movement, you realize, is that of a pack of lagufaeth that have swarmed the junk.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Eyes shielded with an open palm, [Specified 1] squints. "Stranded ship, captain. There's movement. Might be survivors."

You look. Dark shapes move above the weathered hull.

"Big old junk like that," [Specified 2] mutters, "could have some nice guns. Who knows what else."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave it be.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Prepare the cannons. Send it to the ocean's floor."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Terrify them with an ability.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"With what? We don't have any cannonballs."

[Specified 2] coughs.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>The lagufaeth under your baleful gaze, you pour forth essence in a potent blast of pure horror.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 5] nods to you, then focuses on the far ship. After a few moments of concentration, your follower releases a torrential outpouring of concentrated fear.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>With a grating chorus of screeches and hisses, the sea creatures flee the deck, diving over the rails to vanish into the depths.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm going aboard."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Ship] shivers as the guns blaze, sending balls of lead through the stranded junk.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Player Ship] releases a volley of lead balls that crash harmlessly into the water.

The light breeze carries the screeching and hissing of the lagufaeth on deck.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>The lagufaeth leap from the deck and vanish into the water.

You watch as the ship rolls over and sinks beneath the waves.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 2] grins. "My pleasure, captain." 

With a bevy of shouted orders, the cannoneer vanishes into the hold.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Specified 2] snaps to attention. "Aye, captain. It's your lead to waste."

With a bevy of shouted orders, the cannoneer vanishes into the hold.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>The skiff bumps against the junk, and you scale the side of the lagufaeth-infested ship...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
